WEBVTT

00:00:00.068 --> 00:00:10.468
Subtitle Provide by kisskh.org Translator [Admin.@YNG]

00:00:10.468 --> 00:00:12.470
[grandiose, dramatic music playing]

00:00:16.558 --> 00:00:18.934
[Wednesday] William Faulkner said,
"The past is never dead."

00:00:18.935 --> 00:00:20.019
[thunder rumbling]

00:00:20.020 --> 00:00:21.813
"It's not even the past."

00:00:22.731 --> 00:00:25.025
In fact, it's all still happening.

00:00:26.317 --> 00:00:28.778
If Isaac's goal is to save his sister,

00:00:30.613 --> 00:00:32.281
why kidnap Pugsley?

00:00:32.282 --> 00:00:33.991
[man] All right. Spread out, guys.

00:00:33.992 --> 00:00:35.826
- You, that way.
- [woman] Pugsley!

00:00:35.827 --> 00:00:37.870
[Wednesday] What does
a brain-eating genius need

00:00:37.871 --> 00:00:39.956
with my half-wit brother?

00:00:43.209 --> 00:00:44.251
No sign of your son.

00:00:44.252 --> 00:00:47.087
- [Morticia exhales sharply]
- Any idea why someone would kidnap him?

00:00:47.088 --> 00:00:48.881
It's a total mystery, Sheriff.

00:00:48.882 --> 00:00:51.842
Can you think of anyone
who has a grudge against your family?

00:00:51.843 --> 00:00:53.552
Could this be some kind of revenge?

00:00:53.553 --> 00:00:56.139
Are you blaming us
for our son's kidnapping?

00:00:57.015 --> 00:00:59.016
The search parties
will run through the night.

00:00:59.017 --> 00:01:02.144
Parents who were at the gala
have already left with their kids.

00:01:02.145 --> 00:01:03.687
All other students will be packed up

00:01:03.688 --> 00:01:06.107
and on their way home
by tomorrow afternoon.

00:01:07.233 --> 00:01:09.819
I'm sorry. We're doing everything we can.

00:01:10.862 --> 00:01:14.031
[Morticia] I sent your father and Lurch
out to join the search parties.

00:01:14.032 --> 00:01:15.407
They won't find Pugsley.

00:01:15.408 --> 00:01:16.700
Isaac's too smart.

00:01:16.701 --> 00:01:20.704
{\an8}You need to work together, and to pool
your psychic abilities to locate him.

00:01:20.705 --> 00:01:22.873
My mother is a Dove
who's blind to malevolence,

00:01:22.874 --> 00:01:26.544
and my psychic ability is currently
on an unauthorized leave of absence.

00:01:27.712 --> 00:01:31.423
That's why you must turn
to the other Raven in your family.

00:01:31.424 --> 00:01:32.466
My mother?

00:01:32.467 --> 00:01:35.344
These are desperate times.

00:01:35.345 --> 00:01:37.889
[wry, impish music playing]

00:01:44.229 --> 00:01:47.815
Mama, I appreciate you
coming back on such short notice.

00:01:47.816 --> 00:01:50.734
Why would anyone
bother kidnapping Pugsley?

00:01:50.735 --> 00:01:52.945
Not to cast aspersions,

00:01:52.946 --> 00:01:55.614
but I know higher value corpses
than that boy.

00:01:55.615 --> 00:01:57.951
His kidnapper
isn't looking for ransom money.

00:01:58.451 --> 00:02:01.913
He's being used as a pawn
to keep us away, or a ploy to draw us in.

00:02:03.414 --> 00:02:06.626
So many delightful memories of this room.

00:02:07.335 --> 00:02:10.212
I can still hear
the terrified shrieks of my classmates

00:02:10.213 --> 00:02:12.881
during Rotwood's
Advanced Possession Class.

00:02:12.882 --> 00:02:14.508
[Hester chuckles]

00:02:14.509 --> 00:02:16.052
Scaredy-cats.

00:02:18.471 --> 00:02:19.513
[Morticia exhales]

00:02:19.514 --> 00:02:21.599
[eerie music playing]

00:02:23.810 --> 00:02:26.396
This does require
actual physical connection.

00:02:33.778 --> 00:02:37.281
Now we must clear our minds
of all past grievances.

00:02:37.282 --> 00:02:40.534
My past grievances are like fine wine.
They get better with age.

00:02:40.535 --> 00:02:41.619
Likewise.

00:02:45.456 --> 00:02:47.833
Doves and Ravens together ignite

00:02:47.834 --> 00:02:51.462
With wings of darkness and piercing eyes

00:02:52.005 --> 00:02:54.923
Guide us to truth through night and morn

00:02:54.924 --> 00:02:57.968
To this let our powers be sworn

00:02:57.969 --> 00:03:00.137
I didn't drive all this way
to hold hands in the dark.

00:03:00.138 --> 00:03:02.264
How long do we have to keep this up?

00:03:02.265 --> 00:03:05.310
Mama! For once just be quiet.
We're trying to find Pugsley.

00:03:07.103 --> 00:03:08.103
I feel something.

00:03:08.104 --> 00:03:10.606
- I feel it too.
- Do you sense it, Wednesday?

00:03:10.607 --> 00:03:13.484
[ominous music building]

00:03:16.321 --> 00:03:18.323
[scraping in distance]

00:03:20.992 --> 00:03:22.118
Hurry, Gomez!

00:03:24.412 --> 00:03:26.623
No one will ever know we were here.

00:03:32.629 --> 00:03:34.631
[jauntily macabre intro music playing]

00:04:35.483 --> 00:04:36.484
[music trails off]

00:04:37.402 --> 00:04:38.569
[gasps]

00:04:39.445 --> 00:04:41.822
I saw you and Father
burying Isaac under the Skull Tree

00:04:41.823 --> 00:04:43.825
back when you were students.

00:04:45.702 --> 00:04:48.830
If there was ever a time to unburden
yourself of the truth, now is it.

00:04:54.168 --> 00:04:55.794
You've wasted enough of my time.

00:04:55.795 --> 00:04:57.171
The night of Isaac's accident,

00:04:58.089 --> 00:04:59.590
your father and I

00:05:00.258 --> 00:05:02.051
were at his laboratory

00:05:03.261 --> 00:05:04.928
in Iago Tower.

00:05:04.929 --> 00:05:07.597
[gloomy, dramatic music playing]

00:05:07.598 --> 00:05:12.269
Isaac was certain his machine
would permanently cure Francoise.

00:05:12.270 --> 00:05:15.481
That she would never again
live in fear of turning into a Hyde.

00:05:16.607 --> 00:05:21.279
But the machine required
a great amount of energy to power it.

00:05:21.904 --> 00:05:23.405
And for that,

00:05:23.406 --> 00:05:25.950
Isaac turned to his best friend.

00:05:26.534 --> 00:05:27.368
Father.

00:05:31.497 --> 00:05:34.000
What could Gomez
have possibly contributed?

00:05:34.876 --> 00:05:39.213
[Morticia] Back then,
Gomez was just as electrifying as Pugsley.

00:05:40.256 --> 00:05:43.884
And Gomez was more than happy
to help his friend.

00:05:43.885 --> 00:05:46.304
But Isaac tricked him.

00:05:48.097 --> 00:05:50.058
He needed more than a spark.

00:05:53.936 --> 00:05:55.312
Unbeknownst to Francoise,

00:05:55.313 --> 00:05:59.400
Isaac was willing to sacrifice
your father's life to save hers.

00:05:59.901 --> 00:06:02.402
He even dug your father's grave

00:06:02.403 --> 00:06:04.780
under the Skull Tree in preparation.

00:06:04.781 --> 00:06:06.783
[dramatic music intensifies]

00:06:08.618 --> 00:06:09.577
[screaming]

00:06:16.584 --> 00:06:18.251
[Morticia] By the time I arrived,

00:06:18.252 --> 00:06:21.214
my darling Gomez was close to death.

00:06:22.006 --> 00:06:26.594
My sabotage
sent the machine into a frenzy.

00:06:36.229 --> 00:06:38.522
Francoise, she survived the explosion,

00:06:38.523 --> 00:06:39.607
but Isaac didn't.

00:06:40.316 --> 00:06:42.234
And as for your father,

00:06:42.235 --> 00:06:46.614
the experience permanently robbed him
of his Outcast ability.

00:06:48.449 --> 00:06:49.450
Hmm.

00:06:50.660 --> 00:06:51.660
Why cover it up?

00:06:51.661 --> 00:06:53.829
Because Augustus Stonehurst threatened us.

00:06:53.830 --> 00:06:55.997
We knew he built Isaac the lab in secret.

00:06:55.998 --> 00:06:58.875
If we breathed a word,
he would've turned us in for murder.

00:06:58.876 --> 00:07:00.169
Hurry, Gomez.

00:07:01.587 --> 00:07:03.423
No one will ever know we were here.

00:07:04.257 --> 00:07:07.343
So you buried Isaac
in the same grave he intended for Father?

00:07:11.848 --> 00:07:12.932
Yes.

00:07:13.558 --> 00:07:15.100
Isaac must be trying again.

00:07:15.101 --> 00:07:17.394
This time using
Pugsley as the power source.

00:07:17.395 --> 00:07:20.189
That Addams headstone,
the one I saw in my premonition,

00:07:20.690 --> 00:07:21.898
must have Pugsley's name on it.

00:07:21.899 --> 00:07:23.317
[sighs]

00:07:24.402 --> 00:07:29.114
I think it's best that you and Thing
go with Grandmama until Pugsley is found.

00:07:29.115 --> 00:07:31.992
For once, your mother and I
are in agreement.

00:07:31.993 --> 00:07:34.661
[Morticia] These are our sins, Wednesday.

00:07:34.662 --> 00:07:36.038
We will face them.

00:07:37.707 --> 00:07:39.416
I won't put you in danger again.

00:07:39.417 --> 00:07:40.501
Too late.

00:07:59.604 --> 00:08:00.605
[Ajax] I'm sorry.

00:08:01.814 --> 00:08:03.524
You deserve better than that.

00:08:06.277 --> 00:08:08.487
[Enid] I didn't realize
we were back on speaking terms.

00:08:08.488 --> 00:08:10.072
It took me a minute.

00:08:11.115 --> 00:08:12.200
But I'm ready to be friends.

00:08:14.535 --> 00:08:16.120
If that's cool with you.

00:08:18.498 --> 00:08:19.999
I'd like that very much.

00:08:21.959 --> 00:08:23.543
Why the change of heart?

00:08:23.544 --> 00:08:25.879
[sweet, gentle music playing]

00:08:25.880 --> 00:08:28.299
I realized that
our breakup wasn't about me.

00:08:29.300 --> 00:08:31.469
You know, it's nobody's fault
that your feelings changed.

00:08:32.053 --> 00:08:36.057
So I can either be angry about it,
or I can just accept it and move on.

00:08:37.975 --> 00:08:39.392
Actually, Bianca told me that.

00:08:39.393 --> 00:08:40.477
[both chuckle]

00:08:40.478 --> 00:08:42.313
She can be very persuasive.

00:08:58.829 --> 00:08:59.788
[exhales]

00:08:59.789 --> 00:09:00.997
[gasps]

00:09:00.998 --> 00:09:04.626
Please tell me that you're done
with lying wolves and beta-gorgons.

00:09:04.627 --> 00:09:06.753
I put together
a list of potential boyfriends.

00:09:06.754 --> 00:09:10.298
I already cross-referenced them
based on compatible social media profiles.

00:09:10.299 --> 00:09:12.008
Once you've narrowed it down,

00:09:12.009 --> 00:09:14.678
I can pay each one an invisible visit.

00:09:14.679 --> 00:09:17.013
See what they've left out of their bios.

00:09:17.014 --> 00:09:18.181
Hmm.

00:09:18.182 --> 00:09:19.976
I appreciate the assist,

00:09:20.476 --> 00:09:24.104
but I think I'm gonna rip a page
out of the Wednesday Addams playbook

00:09:24.105 --> 00:09:25.648
and take a break from romance.

00:09:29.902 --> 00:09:31.696
It's not very fun

00:09:32.321 --> 00:09:34.824
to be tied up and treated like a pet...

00:09:36.284 --> 00:09:37.285
is it?

00:09:37.785 --> 00:09:39.494
"Mystery meat sandwich!"

00:09:39.495 --> 00:09:41.122
"Your favorite."

00:09:43.124 --> 00:09:44.165
Conserve your energy.

00:09:44.166 --> 00:09:45.418
You're gonna need it.

00:09:48.546 --> 00:09:50.965
I wish I was at least
in one of these pictures.

00:09:53.718 --> 00:09:57.263
I never understood
your desire for a Normie life.

00:09:59.098 --> 00:10:03.269
But... knowing what Stonehurst
did to you in that lab...

00:10:06.272 --> 00:10:08.941
Neither of us got
the end that we deserved.

00:10:10.818 --> 00:10:12.403
That changes tonight.

00:10:16.782 --> 00:10:17.824
Promise me,

00:10:17.825 --> 00:10:19.743
no matter what happens,

00:10:19.744 --> 00:10:20.911
you'll do it.

00:10:21.537 --> 00:10:22.913
What we discussed.

00:10:25.082 --> 00:10:26.375
I need your word.

00:10:32.173 --> 00:10:35.675
I made Hyde tracks about 20 miles north
and dropped Pugsley's costume,

00:10:35.676 --> 00:10:37.928
then made an anonymous tip like you said.

00:10:38.429 --> 00:10:40.347
Good, huh?

00:10:40.348 --> 00:10:42.891
That'll keep the cops off our trail.

00:10:42.892 --> 00:10:47.854
Now, it's time to position
your old flame onto the board.

00:10:47.855 --> 00:10:49.773
Wednesday will know she's being played.

00:10:49.774 --> 00:10:53.568
Yeah, an Addams...
would never sacrifice one of their own.

00:10:53.569 --> 00:10:55.154
Not even a pawn.

00:10:56.072 --> 00:10:58.532
And that emotional weakness

00:10:59.283 --> 00:11:01.035
will be our checkmate.

00:11:02.703 --> 00:11:03.912
[Enid] Any Pugsley update?

00:11:03.913 --> 00:11:06.206
Still missing. But he's alive.

00:11:06.207 --> 00:11:08.375
Isaac is hellbent on saving his sister.

00:11:08.376 --> 00:11:11.628
I know he needs Pugsley.
Just need to figure out when and where.

00:11:11.629 --> 00:11:13.755
[Agnes] Crap. He's here.

00:11:13.756 --> 00:11:14.757
Who?

00:11:15.633 --> 00:11:16.550
[Enid] Isaac?

00:11:17.134 --> 00:11:18.802
No. My dad.

00:11:18.803 --> 00:11:21.888
He usually sends
some rando assistant to collect me.

00:11:21.889 --> 00:11:23.723
Your mom couldn't come get you?

00:11:23.724 --> 00:11:26.852
She's busy with
her new Normie husband and baby.

00:11:27.436 --> 00:11:29.979
I was the mistake
that kept her and my dad together

00:11:29.980 --> 00:11:31.523
long past their sell-by date.

00:11:31.524 --> 00:11:33.359
Gunpowder, penicillin, the rack.

00:11:34.235 --> 00:11:35.528
Those were all mistakes.

00:11:36.987 --> 00:11:39.989
I just want to say that I love us.

00:11:39.990 --> 00:11:41.449
We're like the three musketeers.

00:11:41.450 --> 00:11:42.450
Careful.

00:11:42.451 --> 00:11:43.536
[Agnes's dad] Agnes!

00:11:44.286 --> 00:11:46.038
Bye. See you next year.

00:11:47.331 --> 00:11:49.916
I wish I could help,
but I have to get to the Lupin cages.

00:11:49.917 --> 00:11:51.584
Capri read me the riot act.

00:11:51.585 --> 00:11:53.420
Lock in early and stay calm.

00:11:53.421 --> 00:11:56.214
So I have my meditation app,
my fave playlist,

00:11:56.215 --> 00:11:58.466
and an extra supply of colloidal silver.

00:11:58.467 --> 00:11:59.843
[breathes deeply]

00:11:59.844 --> 00:12:01.595
What could go wrong, right?

00:12:02.388 --> 00:12:04.515
I'll be there
first thing in the morning to let you out.

00:12:05.975 --> 00:12:07.017
Promise?

00:12:09.687 --> 00:12:10.646
[chuckles softly]

00:12:11.397 --> 00:12:13.356
You. We're waking the dead again.

00:12:13.357 --> 00:12:15.358
How long until
your corpse moths are airborne?

00:12:15.359 --> 00:12:17.694
Unfortunately,
they're permanently grounded.

00:12:17.695 --> 00:12:20.448
Corpse moths only have
a 36-hour life cycle.

00:12:23.075 --> 00:12:24.492
Wednesday, I'm really sorry.

00:12:24.493 --> 00:12:26.536
Pugsley wanted to be my friend
and I blew him off.

00:12:26.537 --> 00:12:29.080
Maybe if I'd been nicer,
he wouldn't have felt the need

00:12:29.081 --> 00:12:30.832
to become BFFs with a zombie.

00:12:30.833 --> 00:12:32.584
I am my brother's keeper.

00:12:32.585 --> 00:12:34.794
I simply should have caged him
for his own protection.

00:12:34.795 --> 00:12:38.131
I'm heading to the Hummer shed.
Have to hibernate my bees early.

00:12:38.132 --> 00:12:39.467
Wanna come...

00:12:40.926 --> 00:12:41.927
[bees buzzing]

00:12:43.846 --> 00:12:46.348
["Miss You" by the Rapture
playing over radio]

00:12:48.017 --> 00:12:50.019
[upbeat dance-punk song continuing]

00:12:51.771 --> 00:12:52.688
[Eugene gasps]

00:12:53.522 --> 00:12:55.024
[chilling music playing]

00:12:57.151 --> 00:12:58.652
[music crescendos, trails off]

00:13:02.114 --> 00:13:04.073
Wednesday,
I'm on my way to see your parents.

00:13:04.074 --> 00:13:05.784
A hiker found Pugsley's costume.

00:13:05.785 --> 00:13:08.578
I'm redeploying the search
from Jericho to Burlington.

00:13:08.579 --> 00:13:10.456
Sounds like a ploy
to draw you off the scent.

00:13:11.123 --> 00:13:13.459
I follow evidence, not hunches.

00:13:14.835 --> 00:13:17.213
Finally, I get my office back.

00:13:18.422 --> 00:13:22.425
Dort's crashing downfall
has validated my legacy.

00:13:22.426 --> 00:13:26.429
The board will now look back upon
the Weems era with fondness.

00:13:26.430 --> 00:13:30.225
Nevermore clearly needs
a steady hand on the rudder.

00:13:30.226 --> 00:13:33.186
A leader of impeccable moral character.

00:13:33.187 --> 00:13:35.648
You covered up Rowan's murder
and the existence of a Hyde.

00:13:36.941 --> 00:13:38.526
Mistakes were made.

00:13:39.151 --> 00:13:41.152
But that's all in the past.

00:13:41.153 --> 00:13:43.280
[footsteps approaching]

00:13:45.533 --> 00:13:47.325
I went out to the Hummers shed.

00:13:47.326 --> 00:13:49.869
Slurp was there,
except he looks totally human.

00:13:49.870 --> 00:13:51.037
He told me to give you this.

00:13:51.038 --> 00:13:54.499
Said if I breathe a word to anyone else,
he'd come for me.

00:13:54.500 --> 00:13:56.417
Wednesday, I'm scared.

00:13:56.418 --> 00:13:58.546
Go back to your dorm. Lock the door.

00:13:59.129 --> 00:14:00.130
Now!

00:14:02.883 --> 00:14:05.344
[dire, suspenseful music playing]

00:14:22.862 --> 00:14:25.906
Isaac thinks he can
lure me out to finish me off.

00:14:26.657 --> 00:14:28.117
[muffled struggling]

00:14:30.703 --> 00:14:32.580
When you get a clear shot...

00:14:34.790 --> 00:14:36.750
put a bolt in his zombie brain.

00:14:49.972 --> 00:14:51.639
Tyler warned me you were formidable.

00:14:51.640 --> 00:14:55.476
And now I've witnessed
the havoc you can wreak.

00:14:55.477 --> 00:14:58.939
Give me my brother, crawl back
into your hole, and stay dead this time.

00:14:59.440 --> 00:15:02.276
- I know what you did to my father.
- Yet I'm the one who died.

00:15:02.860 --> 00:15:05.237
Thanks to him and your dear mother.

00:15:05.905 --> 00:15:09.699
Why don't you let your brother
pay for their mistakes,

00:15:09.700 --> 00:15:10.783
and we'll call it even?

00:15:10.784 --> 00:15:12.328
You don't have the machine.

00:15:12.828 --> 00:15:14.621
Willow Hill and Iago Tower
have been destroyed.

00:15:14.622 --> 00:15:16.539
It would take months to rebuild.

00:15:16.540 --> 00:15:19.209
By the time you did,
it'd be too late to save your sister.

00:15:24.214 --> 00:15:26.090
I... I applaud the effort.

00:15:26.091 --> 00:15:27.383
You keep me talking

00:15:27.384 --> 00:15:29.970
while your faithful right hand
takes his shot.

00:15:34.308 --> 00:15:35.309
Gotcha.

00:15:41.231 --> 00:15:43.192
Except he's never been yours.

00:15:44.318 --> 00:15:45.194
He's mine.

00:15:46.779 --> 00:15:49.740
Turns out your parents
didn't kill all of me that night.

00:16:07.925 --> 00:16:08.967
Cute.

00:16:08.968 --> 00:16:11.302
Imagine my surprise
when I saw my right hand

00:16:11.303 --> 00:16:14.055
wandering the halls
of Willow Hill without me.

00:16:14.056 --> 00:16:18.060
And a DaVinci...
is nothing without his right hand.

00:16:21.814 --> 00:16:24.566
Your mother cut it off.

00:16:29.154 --> 00:16:33.826
Causing my machine
to go out of control and explode.

00:16:34.368 --> 00:16:38.121
The power surge must have
somehow animated my hand.

00:16:38.122 --> 00:16:40.374
In your case,
the part is greater than the whole.

00:16:57.099 --> 00:16:59.101
[ghastly, suspenseful music playing]

00:17:16.660 --> 00:17:18.412
Now I am complete.

00:17:25.669 --> 00:17:27.129
The Addams family

00:17:27.880 --> 00:17:30.257
ends tonight.

00:17:32.551 --> 00:17:34.136
Starting with you.

00:18:03.207 --> 00:18:04.957
[Isaac] We have
an appointment at Iago Tower.

00:18:04.958 --> 00:18:08.629
Your pathetic little life
will finally have a purpose.

00:18:09.630 --> 00:18:11.632
[Pugsley struggling in distance]

00:18:14.218 --> 00:18:15.219
[gasps]

00:18:19.765 --> 00:18:20.765
[sighs]

00:18:20.766 --> 00:18:22.851
[gentle, fraught music playing]

00:18:34.446 --> 00:18:35.822
[screams excitedly]

00:18:35.823 --> 00:18:38.200
[both chuckle happily]

00:18:38.867 --> 00:18:41.745
Now we can finally fix our family.

00:18:42.246 --> 00:18:43.288
Hello!

00:18:45.582 --> 00:18:47.459
- Come on.
- [Pugsley grunts]

00:18:49.878 --> 00:18:53.214
{\an8}[meditation app guide]
Take a deep breath in, and slowly exhale.

00:18:53.215 --> 00:18:55.424
{\an8}Now visualize the wolf within.

00:18:55.425 --> 00:18:57.927
{\an8}A powerful but gentle spirit.

00:18:57.928 --> 00:19:00.721
Be mindful that tonight
belongs to tranquility...

00:19:00.722 --> 00:19:02.056
Enid! I need you.

00:19:02.057 --> 00:19:05.726
- Agnes? I thought you left.
- I couldn't abandon Wednesday.

00:19:05.727 --> 00:19:07.980
So I ditched my dad
when he stopped for gas.

00:19:08.564 --> 00:19:10.898
Isaac buried Wednesday
under the Skull Tree.

00:19:10.899 --> 00:19:11.984
And I can't dig her out.

00:19:13.026 --> 00:19:14.652
What? Oh my God.

00:19:14.653 --> 00:19:16.612
- Where's Thing?
- Longer story.

00:19:16.613 --> 00:19:19.700
I'll fill you in on the way.
We haven't got much time!

00:19:20.325 --> 00:19:22.034
[rousing, suspenseful music playing]

00:19:22.035 --> 00:19:24.163
[Enid] Wednesday, we're here! Hang on!

00:19:28.292 --> 00:19:30.002
I hear a heartbeat, but it's weak.

00:19:38.218 --> 00:19:39.970
We aren't gonna get to her in time.

00:19:40.512 --> 00:19:42.681
No, no, no.

00:19:45.475 --> 00:19:48.020
[dramatic choral music playing]

00:19:49.938 --> 00:19:51.565
[Enid] I'm not strong enough like this.

00:19:54.318 --> 00:19:55.944
You won't be able to turn back.

00:19:56.612 --> 00:19:57.779
You're an Alpha.

00:19:58.530 --> 00:19:59.865
I can't let her die.

00:20:02.326 --> 00:20:04.828
[Enid crying out]

00:20:06.371 --> 00:20:07.372
[Enid snarling]

00:20:19.885 --> 00:20:23.388
[Agnes panting]

00:20:24.848 --> 00:20:28.143
Wednesday, wake up. Wake up!

00:20:34.691 --> 00:20:36.401
Please. Please.

00:20:39.029 --> 00:20:40.030
I enjoyed that.

00:20:45.452 --> 00:20:46.453
Enid?

00:20:50.123 --> 00:20:51.959
It was the only way to save you.

00:21:00.342 --> 00:21:02.344
[snarling]

00:21:03.428 --> 00:21:05.597
Go track her. Now!

00:21:07.099 --> 00:21:09.101
[Morticia breathlessly]
Wednesday! Wednesday!

00:21:10.560 --> 00:21:12.437
Thank the spirits.

00:21:15.524 --> 00:21:16.692
Or just one in particular.

00:21:17.359 --> 00:21:20.486
If you don't hurry,
you'll have nothing left to save.

00:21:20.487 --> 00:21:21.947
Where's Pugsley?

00:21:35.168 --> 00:21:37.087
It's all still here.

00:21:39.840 --> 00:21:40.673
Good.

00:21:40.674 --> 00:21:43.134
How are we gonna put
this junk back together?

00:21:43.135 --> 00:21:44.303
[Isaac] We're not.

00:21:46.513 --> 00:21:47.514
I am.

00:21:50.267 --> 00:21:54.021
["Toccata and Fugue in D minor"
by Bach playing over gramophone]

00:22:22.549 --> 00:22:25.426
Even if you never told me
the truth about Thing,

00:22:25.427 --> 00:22:26.927
why didn't you tell him?

00:22:26.928 --> 00:22:29.513
Because sometimes
the truth is better left buried.

00:22:29.514 --> 00:22:31.224
Thing had no memory of Isaac.

00:22:32.017 --> 00:22:36.146
After everything Isaac did to your father,
why burden Thing with that knowledge?

00:22:36.772 --> 00:22:40.816
I like to think whatever trace of goodness
was in Isaac somehow ended up in Thing.

00:22:40.817 --> 00:22:44.111
Except now he's reattached to Isaac,
and he's about to kill your son.

00:22:44.112 --> 00:22:46.906
[grandiose organ music
continuing in distance]

00:22:46.907 --> 00:22:49.033
Mad scientist, clichÃ© soundtrack.

00:22:49.034 --> 00:22:50.034
Perfect.

00:22:50.035 --> 00:22:50.994
Darling,

00:22:52.037 --> 00:22:53.579
you call the sheriff.

00:22:53.580 --> 00:22:55.374
Leave this to us.

00:22:56.666 --> 00:22:58.460
Querida, save our boy.

00:23:12.766 --> 00:23:14.768
[machinery thrumming]

00:23:29.533 --> 00:23:30.909
[music trails off]

00:23:33.453 --> 00:23:34.787
Isaac, are you all right?

00:23:34.788 --> 00:23:36.789
I'm fine. [inhales deeply]

00:23:36.790 --> 00:23:38.500
Secure the power source.

00:23:53.932 --> 00:23:57.268
I've been waiting
for this moment for 30 years.

00:23:57.269 --> 00:23:58.645
[muffled grunting]

00:24:15.954 --> 00:24:17.204
Get ready.

00:24:17.205 --> 00:24:19.249
We're about to fry your battery.

00:24:30.927 --> 00:24:32.304
It's time, Isaac.

00:24:33.221 --> 00:24:34.055
Do it now.

00:24:36.641 --> 00:24:37.642
Now!

00:24:38.393 --> 00:24:39.728
You promised me.

00:24:57.829 --> 00:24:59.581
[Tyler] Wait! What are you doing?

00:25:00.624 --> 00:25:02.458
Mom, we're here to save you.

00:25:02.459 --> 00:25:04.461
It's too late for me, sweetie.

00:25:05.045 --> 00:25:06.837
This is your time now.

00:25:06.838 --> 00:25:09.132
We can save you from this life.

00:25:10.467 --> 00:25:12.135
Give you a fresh start.

00:25:13.094 --> 00:25:16.014
No, no, you have no right
to take my power from me!

00:25:19.476 --> 00:25:20.644
Love you.

00:25:21.645 --> 00:25:23.687
Don't do this. Please.

00:25:23.688 --> 00:25:24.981
I love you, baby.

00:25:27.734 --> 00:25:29.235
[foreboding music playing]

00:25:29.236 --> 00:25:31.238
[machinery humming]

00:25:34.950 --> 00:25:35.867
[Tyler wails] Mom!

00:25:36.993 --> 00:25:39.913
You take the main staircase.
I'll take the ladder.

00:25:45.043 --> 00:25:46.294
[Tyler] Mom, please!

00:25:49.631 --> 00:25:50.674
Mom!

00:25:54.094 --> 00:25:55.428
We have company.

00:25:56.179 --> 00:25:57.806
[Tyler] Please, don't do this!

00:25:58.848 --> 00:26:00.809
[thrumming intensifies]

00:26:01.393 --> 00:26:02.227
[screams]

00:26:04.563 --> 00:26:06.731
[energy crackling]

00:26:21.371 --> 00:26:22.706
[painful yelling]

00:26:27.877 --> 00:26:30.755
[boys moan painfully]

00:26:40.181 --> 00:26:41.474
Kill me.

00:26:42.225 --> 00:26:44.060
[music crescendos, trails off]

00:26:47.647 --> 00:26:48.690
[crackling slows down]

00:26:51.860 --> 00:26:53.987
- Why?
- I missed.

00:26:59.576 --> 00:27:00.827
[Tyler roaring]

00:27:09.294 --> 00:27:10.503
Tyler, no!

00:27:11.087 --> 00:27:12.213
No!

00:27:16.426 --> 00:27:18.345
Isaac!

00:27:19.721 --> 00:27:20.847
Isaac!

00:27:21.806 --> 00:27:22.807
Isaac.

00:27:28.355 --> 00:27:29.229
[Francoise] It's okay.

00:27:29.230 --> 00:27:31.106
- [muffled] Wednesday?
- Shh.

00:27:31.107 --> 00:27:32.483
[Francoise] It's your mommy.

00:27:32.484 --> 00:27:36.363
I haven't enjoyed a mother-son
relationship like this since Psycho.

00:27:42.577 --> 00:27:44.329
Tyler? Honey?

00:27:47.082 --> 00:27:47.915
Baby--

00:27:47.916 --> 00:27:49.000
[Francoise yells]

00:27:52.754 --> 00:27:53.962
[snarling]

00:27:53.963 --> 00:27:55.757
[foreboding music continuing]

00:28:17.112 --> 00:28:18.113
{\an8}[moaning weakly]

00:28:20.532 --> 00:28:22.409
Hold on, Pugsley. Hold on.

00:28:42.679 --> 00:28:44.848
[both snarling]

00:29:19.048 --> 00:29:19.883
[yelps]

00:29:30.310 --> 00:29:32.312
[deep bellowing]

00:29:37.233 --> 00:29:38.359
Isaac!

00:29:40.028 --> 00:29:41.780
You have something that belongs to me.

00:29:42.906 --> 00:29:44.908
[music builds]

00:29:45.742 --> 00:29:46.826
Come on! Come on!

00:29:48.620 --> 00:29:50.246
[music halts]

00:30:02.091 --> 00:30:04.093
[forlorn, emotional music playing]

00:30:19.776 --> 00:30:20.777
[Santiago] Go.

00:30:21.945 --> 00:30:23.404
Go, go, go!

00:30:28.535 --> 00:30:30.537
[dark, imposing music playing]

00:30:35.750 --> 00:30:36.751
[Tyler bellowing]

00:30:40.171 --> 00:30:41.172
[music trailing off]

00:30:44.259 --> 00:30:46.261
[somber, distraught music playing]

00:31:01.901 --> 00:31:03.444
[Pugsley] Mom. Dad.

00:31:06.573 --> 00:31:07.740
Tish!

00:31:10.577 --> 00:31:11.578
[gasps sharply]

00:31:15.832 --> 00:31:18.209
[Gomez] Help me. Help me with this.

00:31:32.348 --> 00:31:35.393
I guess your premonition
didn't come true after all.

00:31:46.821 --> 00:31:48.780
[Isaac] Because of you,

00:31:48.781 --> 00:31:51.700
I lost the only person I ever truly loved.

00:31:51.701 --> 00:31:54.162
[Gomez] Isaac! Isaac!

00:31:54.746 --> 00:31:55.913
It's over.

00:31:55.914 --> 00:31:57.331
Let my daughter go.

00:31:57.332 --> 00:31:58.999
Sorry, old friend.

00:31:59.000 --> 00:32:02.503
Now you two will know
what real pain feels like.

00:32:04.213 --> 00:32:06.799
One more step, and I snap her neck!

00:32:11.679 --> 00:32:14.765
Thing, we know you're still in there.

00:32:14.766 --> 00:32:16.893
Come back to us, Thing. We love you.

00:32:17.602 --> 00:32:19.061
We're your family!

00:32:19.062 --> 00:32:21.272
This was never part of your family.

00:32:22.106 --> 00:32:23.232
It's a part of me!

00:32:30.907 --> 00:32:32.659
[gasping for breath]

00:32:38.206 --> 00:32:39.540
You missed!

00:32:40.208 --> 00:32:41.209
{\an8}[bones cracking]

00:32:45.880 --> 00:32:47.382
[tense, eerie music playing]

00:32:48.716 --> 00:32:50.093
Come on, Thing.

00:32:52.011 --> 00:32:54.013
[dramatic, frenetic music playing]

00:33:00.687 --> 00:33:01.771
What is happening?

00:33:04.357 --> 00:33:06.651
- Ah!
- Doesn't take a genius to figure that out.

00:33:11.239 --> 00:33:13.116
[grunting]

00:33:26.045 --> 00:33:27.088
[Isaac whimpering]

00:33:45.148 --> 00:33:46.149
[heart ticking]

00:33:47.525 --> 00:33:48.526
[crying out]

00:33:53.197 --> 00:33:54.115
Time's up.

00:34:14.260 --> 00:34:15.762
[dramatic music trailing off]

00:34:22.018 --> 00:34:24.020
[gentle, aching music playing]

00:35:04.477 --> 00:35:05.812
[Wednesday] Welcome back, Thing.

00:35:07.188 --> 00:35:10.441
- [Pugsley chuckles softly]
- [Gomez giggles]

00:35:21.869 --> 00:35:23.871
[somber, introspective music playing]

00:35:35.383 --> 00:35:38.344
Knowing you were cut from
the literal cloth of an evil genius,

00:35:38.970 --> 00:35:40.805
it makes sense why we're so compatible.

00:35:42.932 --> 00:35:44.684
How does it feel
finally knowing the truth?

00:35:47.311 --> 00:35:51.274
That you can't control the past.
But the future is in your own hand.

00:35:54.861 --> 00:35:56.195
What's it going to be?

00:36:05.454 --> 00:36:06.581
[whooshing]

00:36:07.748 --> 00:36:11.294
- What have you been able to figure out?
- This was on a wildlife cam this morning.

00:36:13.379 --> 00:36:14.630
[Wednesday] That's Enid.

00:36:15.214 --> 00:36:16.715
[Agnes] She was heading north,

00:36:16.716 --> 00:36:18.925
just five miles from the Canadian border.

00:36:18.926 --> 00:36:20.177
What about Capri?

00:36:20.178 --> 00:36:23.346
Was she able to provide intel
that could tell us where Enid is going?

00:36:23.347 --> 00:36:24.764
She's MIA.

00:36:24.765 --> 00:36:27.100
Probably on the hunt for her next job,

00:36:27.101 --> 00:36:30.146
now that Nevermore is nevermore.

00:36:38.779 --> 00:36:40.239
[Capri] Hello, Tyler.

00:36:41.741 --> 00:36:44.660
Whoever you are, just walk away.

00:36:47.121 --> 00:36:50.166
We both know
you can't survive out here alone.

00:36:50.917 --> 00:36:52.335
Not for long.

00:36:53.669 --> 00:36:55.212
But I can save you.

00:36:55.213 --> 00:36:57.839
[mysterious, intriguing music playing]

00:36:57.840 --> 00:37:00.592
Yeah, I'm done with mothers and masters.

00:37:00.593 --> 00:37:03.095
I'm not interested in being either.

00:37:06.265 --> 00:37:07.475
I'm offering...

00:37:08.392 --> 00:37:11.686
a support system for people just like you.

00:37:11.687 --> 00:37:13.438
Fellow Hydes,

00:37:13.439 --> 00:37:16.275
hidden away where
the world can't find them.

00:37:19.278 --> 00:37:20.696
You'd be part of a pack,

00:37:21.948 --> 00:37:26.327
creating a bond that transcends
the need for a single master.

00:37:32.583 --> 00:37:33.833
What's in it for you?

00:37:33.834 --> 00:37:36.879
You're a werewolf.
I can smell it from here.

00:37:38.339 --> 00:37:39.924
My father was a Hyde.

00:37:43.844 --> 00:37:45.137
[sighs glumly]

00:37:50.268 --> 00:37:52.185
This isn't gonna
explode in my face, is it?

00:37:52.186 --> 00:37:53.688
A little snack for the road.

00:37:57.024 --> 00:37:58.733
Don't forget to pace yourself.

00:37:58.734 --> 00:38:00.987
Whoa. Thanks.

00:38:01.487 --> 00:38:03.446
You know, I was thinking,

00:38:03.447 --> 00:38:06.074
over the break, if you're not too busy,

00:38:06.075 --> 00:38:07.660
you could come for a visit?

00:38:08.828 --> 00:38:10.871
Really? To your actual house?

00:38:11.539 --> 00:38:13.332
That's what friends do, right?

00:38:18.004 --> 00:38:19.171
Hmm.

00:38:20.214 --> 00:38:21.257
Wednesday.

00:38:23.009 --> 00:38:24.010
Wait.

00:38:25.845 --> 00:38:27.888
I would like you to have something.

00:38:30.349 --> 00:38:31.599
Aunt Ophelia's journal.

00:38:31.600 --> 00:38:32.685
Yes.

00:38:33.436 --> 00:38:35.145
As I keep being reminded,

00:38:35.146 --> 00:38:38.274
harboring secrets can have
deadly consequences.

00:38:39.358 --> 00:38:41.861
Every family has dark chapters, Wednesday.

00:38:43.946 --> 00:38:45.448
Including ours.

00:38:46.574 --> 00:38:47.658
Thank you, Mother.

00:38:49.493 --> 00:38:51.828
It's gratifying to see you two together.

00:38:51.829 --> 00:38:53.788
[somber, enchanting music playing]

00:38:53.789 --> 00:38:56.207
Restoring your familial bond

00:38:56.208 --> 00:38:59.378
was the first big step
in regaining your psychic ability.

00:39:01.422 --> 00:39:05.259
Now that it's happened,
I'm taking a well-deserved sabbatical.

00:39:11.390 --> 00:39:16.479
Whoever thought that the person
to keep my spirit alive would be you?

00:39:18.898 --> 00:39:20.941
Until we meet again, Wednesday.

00:39:32.578 --> 00:39:34.497
[Gomez] Whoa, it's sunny out there.

00:39:35.373 --> 00:39:38.709
It will be a relief
sleeping under our own leaky roof tonight.

00:39:39.794 --> 00:39:42.295
Oh, let's get your things. Vamos.

00:39:42.296 --> 00:39:43.546
I won't be going home.

00:39:43.547 --> 00:39:46.383
["Walk Don't Run" by the Surfaris playing]

00:39:46.384 --> 00:39:49.136
[rowdy surf rock continuing]

00:39:57.103 --> 00:39:58.812
[chortling] I got your message.

00:39:58.813 --> 00:40:00.814
I'm always up for a road trip.

00:40:00.815 --> 00:40:03.525
So where to?
Slaughter Beach? Death Valley?

00:40:03.526 --> 00:40:05.653
We're headed north to rescue Enid.

00:40:06.362 --> 00:40:07.612
She's an Alpha.

00:40:07.613 --> 00:40:11.241
Ooh, I hear those puppies got fangs
that can rip you apart like taffy,

00:40:11.242 --> 00:40:13.993
and claws that can
slice you up like lunch meat.

00:40:13.994 --> 00:40:14.994
What fun!

00:40:14.995 --> 00:40:16.372
Go.

00:40:23.879 --> 00:40:27.049
[Wednesday] Another year at Nevermore
ends in carnage and chaos.

00:40:28.217 --> 00:40:30.677
Unanswered questions hover like vultures.

00:40:30.678 --> 00:40:34.432
["Sweet Dreams (String Version)"
by the Hampton Rock String Quartet plays]

00:40:35.766 --> 00:40:39.352
Why did I slice Tyler's bonds
rather than his jugular?

00:40:39.353 --> 00:40:41.939
And will that impulsive
act of mercy become my undoing?

00:40:44.775 --> 00:40:48.194
As for my parents,
their smiles don't erase their lies.

00:40:48.195 --> 00:40:50.156
[dark, moody arrangement continuing]

00:40:52.116 --> 00:40:55.161
Was my mother's gift
of Ophelia's diary an act of trust,

00:40:56.162 --> 00:40:57.872
or silent desperation?

00:41:02.251 --> 00:41:04.044
First I must find Enid.

00:41:06.964 --> 00:41:08.424
I gave her my word.

00:41:08.966 --> 00:41:11.510
But who exactly will return by my side?

00:41:13.345 --> 00:41:14.680
My friend?

00:41:15.222 --> 00:41:17.308
Or the beast that's consumed her?

00:41:22.730 --> 00:41:24.064
[jarring stinger]

00:41:32.031 --> 00:41:33.199
Aunt Ophelia.

00:41:34.116 --> 00:41:36.118
[dark, moody arrangement continuing]

00:41:43.959 --> 00:41:46.378
Secrets are the bedrock
of the Addams family.

00:41:48.214 --> 00:41:50.883
Toxic and festering
just below the surface.

00:42:01.936 --> 00:42:03.270
[Hester] Ophelia!

00:42:08.943 --> 00:42:11.361
[Wednesday] As I venture into the unknown,

00:42:11.362 --> 00:42:14.573
I am determined to exhume
every lie and deception,

00:42:15.157 --> 00:42:16.450
or die trying.

00:42:17.618 --> 00:42:20.370
Sounds like a perfect vacation to me.

00:42:20.371 --> 00:42:21.455
[raven caws]

00:42:22.164 --> 00:42:24.166
[jauntily macabre outro music playing]